{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SaintVenantPDE",
        "description": "Full 1D Saint-Venant PDE system for surface overland flow: mass conservation ∂h̃/∂t = −∂q/∂l + (P − I) and momentum conservation ∂q/∂t = −∂F/∂l + g·h̃·(S₀ − Sᶠ), where the momentum flux F = q²/h̃ + g·h̃²/2 is an auxiliary PDE unknown. Migrated from EnvironmentalTransport.jl@a48559c4 src/surface_runoff.jl:117 (SaintVenantPDE builder; PDESystem returned at line 193). MIGRATION STATUS: structure-only (no inline tests — blocked by gt-vzwk: Python CI runner rejects PDE spatial dims; Julia PDE runner required for numerical validation) and blocked on other:discretization-plan (MOLFiniteDifference spatial discretization config not yet in ESM Domain schema). The 1D spatial variable l is the along-slope coordinate; the sibling SurfaceRunoff component (surface_runoff_component.esm) is the single-node ODE reduction of this same PDE system with the spatial-divergence terms dqdl and dFdl exposed as input parameters.",
        "tags": [
            "environmental_transport",
            "surface-runoff",
            "overland-flow",
            "saint-venant",
            "pde",
            "hydrology",
            "manning-friction",
            "wang-2020",
            "method-of-lines"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-30T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "EnvironmentalTransport.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-0n74)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Wang, Z., Timlin, D., Kouznetsov, M., Fleisher, D., Li, S., Tully, K., & Reddy, V. (2020). Coupled model of surface runoff and surface-subsurface water movement. Advances in Water Resources, 137, 103499.",
                "doi": "10.1016/j.advwatres.2019.103499"
            }
        ]
    },
    "domains": {
        "saint_venant_domain": {
            "independent_variable": "t",
            "spatial": {
                "l": { "min": 0.0, "max": 100.0, "units": "m", "grid_spacing": 1.0 }
            },
            "element_type": "Float64"
        }
    },
    "models": {
        "SaintVenantPDE": {
            "domain": "saint_venant_domain",
            "system_kind": "pde",
            "reference": {
                "doi": "10.1016/j.advwatres.2019.103499",
                "notes": "source_ref: EnvironmentalTransport.jl@a48559c4114eb9f06668ecf9f06235aad20f63f0:src/surface_runoff.jl:117 (function SaintVenantPDE; PDESystem returned at line 193)\n\nThe upstream SaintVenantPDE builder constructs a MTK PDESystem with:\n  - independent variables: t (time), l (along-slope length, m)\n  - state unknowns: h_tilde(t,l), q_flux(t,l), F_mom(t,l) — see note on F_mom below\n  - parameters: P_rate, I_rate, S_0_slope, n_mann, g_grav, h_min, h_bc, q_bc, n_ref, q_ref, h_ref\n  - 3 PDEs + 9 boundary/initial conditions\n\nThe three equations (Wang et al. 2020, Eq. 1):\n  eq1 — Mass conservation (Eq. 1a):\n    ∂h̃/∂t = −∂q/∂l + (P_rate − I_rate)\n  eq2 — Momentum conservation (Eq. 1b):\n    ∂q/∂t = −∂F/∂l + g_grav·max(h̃, h_min)·(S₀ − Sᶠ)\n    where Sᶠ = ((n_mann/n_ref)·(q/q_ref))² / (max(h̃, h_min)/h_ref)^(10/3)\n  eq3 — Momentum flux auxiliary (Eq. 1b expansion):\n    F = q²/max(h̃, h_min) + g_grav·h̃²/2\n\nF_mom auxiliary variable: the upstream code introduces F_mom explicitly as a PDESystem unknown (rather than inlining ∂F/∂l directly in eq2) to avoid MethodOfLines.jl creating untyped intermediate variables for the spatial derivative. It carries its own initial and boundary conditions (F_bc = q_bc²/max(h_bc,h_min) + g_grav·h_bc²/2).\n\nBoundary conditions (9 total from upstream bcs array):\n  Initial conditions (t=0): h̃(0,l)=h_bc, q(0,l)=q_bc, F(0,l)=F_bc for all l\n  Left boundary  (l=0):     h̃(t,0)=h_bc, q(t,0)=q_bc, F(t,0)=F_bc for all t\n  Right boundary (l=L):     h̃(t,L)=h_bc, q(t,L)=q_bc, F(t,L)=F_bc for all t\n  All are Dirichlet (fixed-value). The upstream code uses h_bc/q_bc as parameters for both left and right spatial boundaries, implementing a uniform fixed-head inflow/outflow condition.\n\nNaming: the upstream @variables use h_tilde(..) and q_flux(..) in ASCII (unlike the sibling @component SurfaceRunoff which uses the combining-tilde h̃). The ESM preserves this ASCII naming. F_mom replaces the upstream F_mom(..) — same name.\n\nNon-dimensionalization: Manning's friction slope Sᶠ raises q/h to fractional powers (10/3). The upstream code divides by unit-valued reference constants n_ref=1.0, q_ref=1.0, h_ref=1.0 so the fractional power bases are dimensionless. These are preserved verbatim.\n\nBLOCKING GAPS:\n  gt-vzwk (PDE-tests): The Python CI runner (earthsci_toolkit.simulate) explicitly rejects\n    PDE systems (UnsupportedDimensionalityError for spatial IVs). No inline tests are\n    included; the minimum-bar load() gate passes. A Julia PDE runner (EarthSciSerialization\n    + ModelingToolkit + MethodOfLines.jl) is required for numerical validation.\n  other:discretization-plan: The upstream SaintVenantPDE builder is designed for\n    MOL discretization via MethodOfLines.jl (MOLFiniteDifference). The ESM Domain schema\n    v0.4.0 carries spatial grid metadata but does not yet encode the discretization\n    method (upwind scheme, WENO order, Rusanov flux, etc.) needed to run the PDE;\n    this is tracked by gap gt-dq0f (v2.1). The ESM encodes the continuous PDE structure;\n    the discretization catalog will add the method spec when the schema supports it.\n\nRelationship to SurfaceRunoff ODE: the sibling surface_runoff_component.esm is the\npoint-wise ODE reduction of this PDE. It exposes dqdl (= ∂q/∂l) and dFdl (= ∂F/∂l)\nas input parameters. This PDE component builds those spatial derivatives from the\nfull h̃(t,l) and q(t,l) spatial fields."
            },
            "variables": {
                "h_tilde": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "shape": ["l"],
                    "description": "Flow depth / ponded water height (Eq. 1a PDE state). Function of time t and along-slope coordinate l. Initial and boundary value h_bc (default 1 mm). Corresponds to h̃(t,l) in upstream Julia code."
                },
                "q_flux": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^2/s",
                    "shape": ["l"],
                    "description": "Surface runoff flux per unit width (Eq. 1b PDE state). Function of time t and along-slope coordinate l. Initial and boundary value q_bc (default 0 m²/s). Corresponds to q_flux(t,l) in upstream Julia code."
                },
                "F_mom": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^3/s^2",
                    "shape": ["l"],
                    "description": "Momentum flux auxiliary PDE unknown: F = q²/max(h̃,h_min) + g·h̃²/2 (Eq. 1b). Listed as an explicit PDESystem unknown in the upstream code to ensure MethodOfLines.jl can discretize ∂F/∂l directly rather than creating untyped intermediate derivatives. Algebraically determined by h_tilde and q_flux at each (t,l) point. Initial and boundary value F_bc = q_bc²/max(h_bc,h_min) + g_grav·h_bc²/2."
                },
                "S_f": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "shape": ["l"],
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "^",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": ["n_mann", "q_flux"]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": ["n_ref", "q_ref"]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    2.0
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "^",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "max",
                                                "args": ["h_tilde", "h_min"]
                                            },
                                            "h_ref"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    3.3333333333333335
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "description": "Manning friction slope Sᶠ = ((n_mann·q)/(n_ref·q_ref))² / (max(h̃,h_min)/h_ref)^(10/3). Dimensionless. Non-dimensionalized by reference constants n_ref=q_ref=h_ref=1.0 so the fractional-power bases are dimensionless ratios. Used in the momentum equation (Eq. 1b) as the friction dissipation term opposing the surface slope S₀. Observed (derived) field; not an explicit PDESystem unknown in the upstream code."
                },
                "g_grav": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s^2",
                    "default": 9.81,
                    "description": "Gravitational acceleration (m/s²). Upstream @constants value; drives the buoyancy term g·h̃·(S₀−Sᶠ) in the momentum equation and the pressure term g·h̃²/2 in the momentum flux. Encoded as type:parameter (schema has no constant type); never overridden in tests or examples."
                },
                "n_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^(-1/3)*s",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Reference Manning coefficient for non-dimensionalization (upstream default 1.0 m^(-1/3)·s). Divides n_mann in the Manning friction slope so the squared base is dimensionless; the unit value changes no numbers."
                },
                "q_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^2/s",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Reference runoff flux for non-dimensionalization (upstream default 1.0 m²/s). Divides q_flux in the Manning friction slope so the squared base is dimensionless; the unit value changes no numbers."
                },
                "h_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Reference flow depth for non-dimensionalization (upstream default 1.0 m). Divides max(h̃,h_min) in the Manning friction slope so the (10/3)-power base is dimensionless; the unit value changes no numbers."
                },
                "S_0_slope": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.01,
                    "description": "Surface slope (dimensionless) — gradient of the soil surface along the flow direction l. Drives the momentum source term g·h̃·(S₀−Sᶠ); when S₀ > Sᶠ the flow accelerates. Upstream default 0.01 (1% slope, used in Wang 2020 doc examples)."
                },
                "n_mann": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^(-1/3)*s",
                    "default": 0.03,
                    "description": "Manning roughness coefficient. Controls friction dissipation via the Manning slope Sᶠ. Larger values produce larger Sᶠ and slower flow. Upstream default 0.03 m^(-1/3)·s (bare soil; Wang 2020 documentation example)."
                },
                "h_min": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1.0e-5,
                    "description": "Minimum flow depth floor (m). Applied via max(h̃, h_min) in the momentum flux F and friction slope Sᶠ to prevent singularities when h̃→0. Upstream h_min default 1e-5 m, kept verbatim."
                },
                "h_bc": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1.0e-3,
                    "description": "Boundary and initial flow depth (m). Applied as a Dirichlet condition at t=0 (initial state) and at l=0 and l=L (spatial boundaries). Upstream h_bc/h_init_val default 1e-3 m (1 mm thin initial film)."
                },
                "q_bc": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^2/s",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Boundary and initial runoff flux (m²/s). Applied as a Dirichlet condition at t=0 and at l=0 and l=L. Upstream q_bc/q_init_val default 0.0 m²/s (flow at rest initially)."
                },
                "P_rate": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 1.9444444444444444e-5,
                    "description": "Precipitation flux density (m/s). Source term in the mass conservation equation (Eq. 1a): ∂h̃/∂t = −∂q/∂l + (P_rate − I_rate). Upstream P_val default = 70 mm/hr = 70/1000/3600 ≈ 1.944e-5 m/s."
                },
                "I_rate": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Infiltration flux density (m/s). Sink term in the mass conservation equation (Eq. 1a): ∂h̃/∂t = −∂q/∂l + (P_rate − I_rate). Upstream I_val default 0.0 m/s (no infiltration — pure surface flow scenario)."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 1a (Wang et al. 2020) — mass conservation: ∂h̃/∂t = −∂q/∂l + (P_rate − I_rate). The ponded depth increases with net precipitation over infiltration and decreases as runoff flows downslope.",
                    "lhs": { "op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["h_tilde"] },
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [ -1.0, { "op": "grad", "args": ["q_flux"], "dim": "l" } ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "-",
                                "args": [ "P_rate", "I_rate" ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 1b (Wang et al. 2020) — momentum conservation: ∂q/∂t = −∂F/∂l + g·max(h̃,h_min)·(S₀−Sᶠ). Runoff flux is driven by the slope-friction imbalance and reduced by the spatial divergence of momentum flux F.",
                    "lhs": { "op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["q_flux"] },
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [ -1.0, { "op": "grad", "args": ["F_mom"], "dim": "l" } ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "g_grav",
                                    { "op": "max", "args": ["h_tilde", "h_min"] },
                                    { "op": "-", "args": ["S_0_slope", "S_f"] }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Momentum flux auxiliary (Eq. 1b): F = q²/max(h̃,h_min) + g·h̃²/2. Listed as a PDESystem unknown in the upstream code so MethodOfLines can discretize ∂F/∂l directly. Algebraically determined at each spatial point from h_tilde and q_flux.",
                    "lhs": "F_mom",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "^", "args": ["q_flux", 2.0] },
                                    { "op": "max", "args": ["h_tilde", "h_min"] }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "g_grav",
                                    { "op": "^", "args": ["h_tilde", 2.0] },
                                    0.5
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "boundary_conditions": {
                "h_tilde_lmin": {
                    "variable": "h_tilde",
                    "side": "lmin",
                    "kind": "dirichlet",
                    "value": "h_bc",
                    "description": "Dirichlet BC at l=0 (upslope boundary): h̃(t,0) = h_bc. Upstream sets this to h_init_val (default 1e-3 m) for all t, representing the inflow boundary condition."
                },
                "h_tilde_lmax": {
                    "variable": "h_tilde",
                    "side": "lmax",
                    "kind": "dirichlet",
                    "value": "h_bc",
                    "description": "Dirichlet BC at l=L (downslope boundary): h̃(t,L) = h_bc. Upstream uses the same h_bc value at both boundaries."
                },
                "q_flux_lmin": {
                    "variable": "q_flux",
                    "side": "lmin",
                    "kind": "dirichlet",
                    "value": "q_bc",
                    "description": "Dirichlet BC at l=0 (upslope boundary): q(t,0) = q_bc. Upstream sets this to q_init_val (default 0 m²/s, no inflow from upslope)."
                },
                "q_flux_lmax": {
                    "variable": "q_flux",
                    "side": "lmax",
                    "kind": "dirichlet",
                    "value": "q_bc",
                    "description": "Dirichlet BC at l=L (downslope boundary): q(t,L) = q_bc. Upstream uses the same q_bc value at both boundaries."
                },
                "F_mom_lmin": {
                    "variable": "F_mom",
                    "side": "lmin",
                    "kind": "dirichlet",
                    "value": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "^", "args": ["q_bc", 2.0] },
                                    { "op": "max", "args": ["h_bc", "h_min"] }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "g_grav",
                                    { "op": "^", "args": ["h_bc", 2.0] },
                                    0.5
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "description": "Dirichlet BC at l=0: F(t,0) = F_bc = q_bc²/max(h_bc,h_min) + g·h_bc²/2. Consistent with the boundary flow state (h_bc, q_bc)."
                },
                "F_mom_lmax": {
                    "variable": "F_mom",
                    "side": "lmax",
                    "kind": "dirichlet",
                    "value": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "^", "args": ["q_bc", 2.0] },
                                    { "op": "max", "args": ["h_bc", "h_min"] }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "g_grav",
                                    { "op": "^", "args": ["h_bc", 2.0] },
                                    0.5
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "description": "Dirichlet BC at l=L: F(t,L) = F_bc = q_bc²/max(h_bc,h_min) + g·h_bc²/2. Consistent with the boundary flow state (h_bc, q_bc)."
                }
            },
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "steady_rainfall_runoff",
                    "description": "Canonical steady rainfall over a 100 m slope (Wang et al. 2020 default parameters): P_rate=70 mm/hr, no infiltration, 1% slope, Manning n=0.03. Starting from a thin initial film (1 mm depth, zero flux), rainfall accumulates and drives downslope runoff. NOTE: requires a PDE-capable runner (Julia EarthSciSerialization + ModelingToolkit + MethodOfLines.jl) — the Python earthsci_toolkit runner does not support spatial PDE simulation (gt-vzwk gap).",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "expression",
                        "values": {
                            "h_tilde": "h_bc",
                            "q_flux": "q_bc",
                            "F_mom": {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "^", "args": ["q_bc", 2.0] },
                                            { "op": "max", "args": ["h_bc", "h_min"] }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "g_grav",
                                            { "op": "^", "args": ["h_bc", 2.0] },
                                            0.5
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "P_rate": 1.9444444444444444e-5,
                        "I_rate": 0.0,
                        "S_0_slope": 0.01,
                        "n_mann": 0.03,
                        "g_grav": 9.81,
                        "h_min": 1.0e-5,
                        "h_bc": 1.0e-3,
                        "q_bc": 0.0,
                        "n_ref": 1.0,
                        "q_ref": 1.0,
                        "h_ref": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 3600.0 },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "depth_profile_t1800",
                            "type": "field_snapshot",
                            "description": "Flow depth h̃(l) profile at t=1800 s (30 min). Rain accumulation produces a depth that increases downslope as runoff collects. NOTE: requires Julia PDE runner (gt-vzwk gap).",
                            "at_time": 1800.0,
                            "x": { "variable": "l", "label": "Along-slope distance l (m)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "h_tilde", "label": "Flow depth h̃ (m)" },
                            "value": { "variable": "h_tilde" }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "flux_profile_t3600",
                            "type": "field_snapshot",
                            "description": "Runoff flux q(l) profile at t=3600 s (1 hr). Peak flux occurs at the downslope end as water collected over the entire slope must drain. NOTE: requires Julia PDE runner (gt-vzwk gap).",
                            "at_time": 3600.0,
                            "x": { "variable": "l", "label": "Along-slope distance l (m)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "q_flux", "label": "Runoff flux q (m²/s)" },
                            "value": { "variable": "q_flux" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "flat_no_rain",
                    "description": "Zero precipitation, zero slope: P_rate=0, I_rate=0, S_0_slope=0. Starting from uniform 1 mm depth at rest, the system should remain at h̃=h_bc, q=0, Sᶠ=0 (no forcing, no friction). This is a structural sanity check: the mass equation gives ∂h̃/∂t = 0 and the momentum equation gives ∂q/∂t = 0, so both fields are constant in time. NOTE: requires Julia PDE runner (gt-vzwk gap).",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "expression",
                        "values": {
                            "h_tilde": "h_bc",
                            "q_flux": "q_bc",
                            "F_mom": {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "^", "args": ["q_bc", 2.0] },
                                            { "op": "max", "args": ["h_bc", "h_min"] }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "g_grav",
                                            { "op": "^", "args": ["h_bc", 2.0] },
                                            0.5
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    },
                    "parameters": {
